content.text: Now I understand the schema. The attendance is tracked per member per event, so "attendance over 20 students" means COUNT(link_to_member) > 20 grouped by event. Let me query for events with attendance > 20 that are not fundraisers.

input.command: sqlite3 -header -column "/Users/david/workspace/claimdb/test_dbs/student_club.sqlite" "SELECT e.event_name, e.type, COUNT(a.link_to_member) as attendance FROM event e JOIN attendance a ON e.event_id = a.link_to_event GROUP BY e.event_id HAVING COUNT(a.link_to_member) > 20 ORDER BY e.event_name;"
